    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer underflow in UL frequency offset estimation\n\n### Summary\nThe `lte_ul_freq_offset_estimation` function in `lte_ul_channel_estimation.c` was experiencing integer underflow when accessing the `alpha` array with negative indices. This caused unexpected large unsigned values downstream in the frequency offset calculation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_ESTIMATION/lte_ul_channel_estimation.c`: \n  - Added bounds checking for `a_idx` variable to prevent array access underflow/overflow\n  - Added check for `nb_rb == 0` to prevent division by zero\n  - Minor formatting cleanup\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain channel conditions with specific RB allocations, the function would access `alpha[a_idx]` with negative `a_idx` values, causing the phase estimation to return incorrect frequency offset values. This manifested as degraded UL synchronization performance and increased BLER in high mobility scenarios.\n\n"
}